3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678f6c0c10c98eace9132218%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-workplace-digital-colleague-employees-pwc-head-davos-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22PwC's%20global%20chairman%20said%20that%20putting%20technology%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20workers%20allows%20them%20to%20view%20AI%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20colleague%26quot%3B%20they%20can%20work%20with.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22shubhangigoel%40insider.com%20(Shubhangi%20Goel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-workplace-digital-colleague-employees-pwc-head-davos-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Trump's%20Day%201%20Order%20To%20End%20Birthright%20Citizenship%20Will%20Impact%20Indians%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump's%20first%20day%20as%20the%2047th%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%20was%20marked%20by%20a%20significant%20move%20to%20reshape%20the%20country's%20immigration%20landscape.%20He%20signed%20an%20executive%20order%20that%20targets%20multiple%20immigration%20laws%2C%20including%20the%20long-standing%20principle%20of%20birthright%20citizenship.%20This%20move%20has%20sparked%20intense%20debate%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20face%20formidable%20legal%20challenges.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAt%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20controversy%20is%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%2C%20which%20grants%20citizenship%20to%20all%20individuals%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20The%2014th%20Amendment%20states%3A%20%26quot%3BAll%20persons%20born%20or%20naturalized%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20subject%20to%20the%20jurisdiction%20thereof%2C%20are%20citizens%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20of%20the%20state%20wherein%20they%20reside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20seeks%20to%20reinterpret%20this%20amendment%2C%20asserting%20that%20children%20born%20to%20undocumented%20parents%20are%20not%20entitled%20to%20automatic%20citizenship.%20This%20drastic%20shift%20in%20policy%20is%20expected%20to%20impact%20millions%20of%20Indian-Americans%20residing%20in%20the%20US%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20been%20awaiting%20green%20cards%20for%20years%20or%20even%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20deemed%20birthright%20citizenship%20as%20%26quot%3Bridiculous%26quot%3B%20and%20claims%20that%20ending%20it%20will%20curb%20illegal%20immigration.%20%26quot%3BThe%2014th%20Amendment%20has%20never%20been%20interpreted%20to%20extend%20citizenship%20universally%20to%20everyone%20born%20within%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20delineated%20in%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20critics%20argue%20that%20this%20move%20will%20only%20serve%20to%20further%20marginalise%20vulnerable%20communities%20and%20create%20uncertainty%20for%20immigrant%20families.%20The%20consequences%20of%20this%20policy%20are%20far-reaching%2C%20with%20potential%20disruptions%20on%20schools%2C%20workplaces%2C%20and%20entire%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20in%20the%20policy%20is%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%2030%20days%20after%20the%20order%20issuance%2C%20a%20move%20set%20to%20ignite%20legal%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20effects%20of%20this%20policy%20will%20be%20on%20Indian%20families%20who%20have%20been%20using%20birth%20tourism%20as%20a%20means%20to%20obtain%20US%20citizenship%20for%20their%20children.%20Birth%20tourism%2C%20which%20involves%20traveling%20to%20the%20US%20to%20give%20birth%2C%20has%20been%20a%20popular%20route%20for%20Mexican%20and%20Indian%20families.%20However%2C%20Trump's%20new%20policy%20is%20expected%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20practice%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau%2C%20about%205%20million%20Indian%20Americans%20are%20currently%20residing%20in%20the%20US%2C%20making%20up%20about%201.47%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20population.%20Of%20these%2C%20only%2034%20per%20cent%20are%20US%20born%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20two-thirds%20are%20immigrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajority%20of%20the%20Indian%20nationals%20that%20are%20currently%20working%20in%20the%20US%20are%20on%20the%20H1-B%20visa%2C%20with%20that%2C%20hundreds%20of%20Indian-origin%20children%20being%20born%20on%20the%20US%20soil%20will%20not%20be%20granted%20automatic%20citizenship%20according%20to%20President%20Trump's%20executive%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union%20(ACLU)%20has%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20Trump's%20executive%20order%2C%20citing%20the%2014th%20Amendment's%20clear%20language%20on%20birthright%20citizenship.%20The%20ACLU%20has%20also%20highlighted%20the%20potential%20for%20mass%20deportations%2C%20family%20separations%2C%20and%20other%20human%20rights%20abuses%20under%20Trump's%20immigration%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20a%20press%20release%2C%20the%20ACLU%20also%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3BImmigrants'%20rights%20advocates%20today%20sued%20the%20Trump%20administration%20over%20its%20executive%20order%20that%20seeks%20to%20strip%20certain%20babies%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States%20of%20their%20U.S.%20citizenship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20battle%20over%20birthright%20citizenship%20and%20immigration%20reform%20intensifies%2C%20the%20future%20of%20millions%20of%20families%20remains%20uncertain.%20Legal%20challenges%20are%20expected%20to%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20trajectory%20of%20this%20controversial%20policy.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20outcome%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20ability%20of%20advocates%2C%20lawmakers%2C%20and%20the%20courts%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20vulnerable%20communities%20and%20uphold%20the%20principles%20of%20justice%20and%20equality%20enshrined%20in%20the%20US%20Constitution.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%